claim.claim-text:
1. A hybrid integrated circuit device comprising: 
a conductive pattern provided at least on a surface of a hybrid integrated circuit substrate; 
at least one of a semiconductor chip and a passive element mounted on the conductive pattern; 
an aluminum fine wire electrically connecting between at least one of the semiconductor chip and the passive element and the conductive pattern; 
a lead connected to the conductive pattern and extended as an output or input to an outside; and 
a thermosetting resin integrally covering the substrate by transfer molding; 
wherein a blanking surface is arranged in a bottom surface of said substrate.

7. A hybrid integrated circuit device comprising: 
a conductive pattern provided at least on a surface of a hybrid integrated circuit substrate; 
at least one of a semiconductor and a passive element fixed on the conductive pattern; 
an aluminum fine wire electrically connecting between the at least one of the semiconductor chip and the passive element and the conductive pattern; 
a lead connected to the conductive pattern and extended as an output or input to an outside; and 
a resin seal body formed of a thermosetting resin covering at least a surface of the substrate by transfer molding.

12. A hybrid integrated circuit device comprising: 
a conductive pattern provided at least on a surface of a hybrid integrated circuit substrate; 
at least one of a semiconductor chip and a passive element mounted on the conductive pattern; 
an aluminum fine wire electrically connecting between the conductive pattern and at least one of the semiconductor chip and the passive element; 
a lead connected to the conductive pattern and extended as an output or input to an outside; and 
a thermosetting resin covering at least a surface of the substrate by transfer molding; 
wherein the thermosetting resin contains a filler having a spherical form, the thermosetting resin having a low viscosity and a fluidity.

17. A method of manufacturing a hybrid integrated circuit device comprising the steps of: 
preparing a hybrid integrated circuit substrate insulation-treated at least in a surface thereof; 
forming a conductive pattern on the substrate; 
mounting at least one of a semiconductor chip and a passive element on the conductive pattern; 
blanking the substrate at a back surface thereof; 
electrically connecting between the at least one of the semiconductor and the passive element and the conductive pattern by the use of an aluminum fine wire; 
connecting the substrate with a lead extending as an output or input to an outside; and 
integrally molding the substrate with a thermosetting resin by transfer molding.
